modules.description: Handles cookie-based session management and persistence, including creation, retrieval, and expiration of session data. Operates on HTTP request and response objects, integrating with cookie headers and backend storage systems like in-memory or file-based stores. Used to implement authenticated web services where user state is maintained across requests.

Provides functions to manage session data in a PostgreSQL database, including generating, retrieving, updating, and clearing sessions with specified expiration times. Operates on session keys (strings), session values (strings), and period values (int64) using a PostgreSQL connection. Used to store and manage user session state with automatic expiration and persistent storage.
